True, neural comparisons move us further: rats and humans have similar brain strains, on the other hand, cockroaches and brains.
But is the brain stem responsible for feelings?
And even if it could be proved in man: how would we want to prove it in rats?
I think rats and other mammals, perhaps even cockroaches (who knows?), have feelings.
