Boxer Rocky Graziano, an abused, violent, unforgettable delinquent from Somebody Up There Likes Me (In the Sign of Hate) by Robert Wise, a role designed for James Dean, taken over after his death, who in 1956 introduced Newman as a true acquaintance.
Sympathic gangster in the absolutely great The Sting (Poraz), Oscar for the best movie in 1973.
Bitter and vindictive pool player in the amazing The Hustler Robert Rossen (1961), the same character will be portrayed in The Color of Money by Martin Scorsese, which will bring him a single Oscar of seven nominations in 1987.
This face wandering for ages, it was him.
And him again.
In his professional career, they compete with different epochs.
Young people know it mainly thanks to the cult Slap Shot George Roy Hill (1977) from the role of Reggie Dunlop, an unconventional hockey coach.
Fans met him again in 1994 at The Hudsucker Proxy Brothers Coen.
He then closed his career as the godfather of the Irish mafia in Road to Perdition Sam Mendes in 2003.
Unlike several movie legends that had left the craft quite soon, Newman remained in the business for a long time, although he condemned Hollywood with his platitudes, pomp and concessions.
The French filmmaker Bertrand Tavernier considered him, not without humor, "a live challenge of underplaying," judging that he pushed him too hard in his performances.
For the beautiful Paul Newman, whose roles came as a tray, the profession was not always so tender.
However, the first lovers played less often than outsiders: neurotics, alcoholics, scumbags, and desperate ones whose decline and rebellion reflected in his perfect features.
As director Newman, he revealed the few known aspects of his shy sensitivity.
His film Rachel, Rachel from 1968 (according to a novel by Canadian Margaret Laurence), in which his wife Joanne Woodward played the lead, presents a sensitive female portrait full of melancholy.
In 1984, Harry and Son dedicated a work of shame and sadness to his son, Scott, whom he lost due to an overdose.
His great friend and former comrade Robert Redford (played together in The Sting and Butch Cassidy and the Sundance Kid) sadly declared: "His presence made my life better and this country better. "
Generosity, love of life, such are the main qualities of a dead actor.
Aside from his legendary career, there is also a great civil rights fighter, ecology, an independent film, an opponent of Hollywood's decline.
We used to see his portrait on bottles of wine vinegar, sauce, cookies and other foods, which might have seemed rather tacky to us, although it was a gag at first.
However, the profits from the sale went to the account of his Foundation for Hard Childhood.
So, rather than being lulled with glory, Newman was engaged in society until the last moment.
He left his five daughters a letter containing these sentences: "Always and to the end your father was grateful to his happy planet.
It was an honor to be here."
And it was an honor for us to be able to watch the career of such a psychic and generous American artist.
And besides, after all, a model citizen.
